}I know you are in love with me and I hope you know that I am in love with you, but this relationship has reached the point where the joy is starting to be drained by the overwhelming amount of pain and anxiety it causes me.

It really hurts me that you continue to lie and hide things from me, despite my repeatedly telling you how important honesty and transparency are to me. I love you so much that I've been trying to tell myself I can live without honesty. That you need time. That eventually it will change. That you've been through so much that you're not ready to trust. That eventually you would stop. I've tried to just suck it up, that I could just...be in a relationship where I didn't trust my partner. I've tried compartmentalizing. Tell myself I could take it for you, for us, for our kids. I've even tried studying stoicism. But I've realized that I'm so unhappy about the dishonesty that it diminishes my ability to enjoy being with you. If I had trouble sleeping or seemed upset and I told you I didn't know why, it was probably this. Instead of feeling safe with you, I'm afraid. I think you aren't honest with me because you think the truth will put our relationship at risk, but please believe me when I tell you that lying is what is putting our relationship at risk.

There was a point where I felt like we could talk about everything. Now I feel like we are constantly hiding things from each other. I've been trying to mask my distrust, anxiety, and emotions from you. I've become paranoid. I don't want to be that person.

I want a relationship based on honesty and trust. Right now, we are very far from that.

I know you well enough to know that you will feel attacked by this and your first impulse will be to push back, to be defensive, to fight me. Please try to resist responding that way. It might help you "win" this encounter or get me to concede to you in the moment, but it will only further damage our relationship. Please try to recognize the only way we get through this by working together, not fighting.

I want you to take some time and really think about what kind of relationship you want with me. I'm hoping it looks a lot more like the relationship I want with you than what we have right now.

If you really love me, you'll tell me everything you've been hiding and lying about and start to take the necessary steps towards rebuilding the trust between us. If not, I think we need to change or end this relationship. There is so much that I love, value and enjoy about being with you, but this is breaking me. I don't know how I will be able to live without you, but I can't continue like this.
